It is known to be very low-gluten, healthy, nutritious and tasty. In earlier days, Emmer Wheat was the most celebrated variety of Wheat and was famously consumed by all. Now-a-days, this variety of wheat is grown on a small scale. Due to heavy dietary fibers, it is a wholesome lunch and is a very good source of energy.
